Unfortunately; padding&#39; does not apply to `table-header-group` and `table-footer-group` so when you get to your mobile views, they are ignored.

You can read more about it here if you want: https://www.w3.org/TR/CSS2/box.html#propdef-padding

I would advise to place the padding into your `row` class such as
```
.row {
  display: table;
  padding: 10px;
 }
```
And then you can style the way you want it.

If you want to keep `table-header-group` and `table-footer-group` in your media query, you cannot leave your padding in `.left`, `.left2`, `.right` or `.right2`.
Hope that it helps :)

